    <briefdescription>
<para>Simple delay class to avoid DOS calls to functions. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Should avoid to cal services too often (e.g. web requests).</para>
<para>Usage: CDelay oDelay(5000); // 5 seconds delay if(oDelay.isDone()) { ... ; oDelay.restart(); }</para>
<para>As an alternative, you can use start(nDelayMillis) to set a new delay time. Use <ref refid="class_c_simple_delay_1addd5489d09b5303a9503f236aa09d126" kindref="member">reset()</ref> to stop the delay. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
